tests.TEST1:
CREATE TABLE Employees (
        EmployeeID INT NOT NULL UNIQUE PRIMARY KEY FOREIGN KEY REFERENCES Departments(DepartmentID),
        FirstName VARCHAR(50),
        LastName VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE,
        dateColumn DATE,
        Email VARCHAR(100),
        DepartmentID INT UNIQUE,
        PRIMARY KEY (EmployeeID),
        FOREIGN KEY (DepartmentID) REFERENCES Departments(DepartmentID)
    );

tests.TEST2: CREATE TABLE Users (ID INT , Name VARCHAR(50));

tests.TEST3: CREATE TABLE Orders (OrderID INT PRIMARY KEY, ProductName VARCHAR(100), Quantity INT);

tests.TEST4: CREATE TABLE Products (ProductID INT UNIQUE, ProductName VARCHAR(100));

tests.TEST5: CREATE TABLE Orders (OrderID INT, CustomerID INT FOREIGN KEY REFERENCES Customers(CustomerID));

tests.TEST6: CREATE TABLE Employees (EmployeeID INT DEFAULT 1001, Name VARCHAR(50));

        BookID INT,

        Author VARCHAR(100),
        PublishedDate DATE,
